"ploneCustom.css. You'll see this if you inspect the HTML head tag of your "
"page using Firebug. If you dig further, you'll probably find that this style"
" sheet is completely empty. By the rules of precedence in the CSS Cascade, "
"any styles in this sheet will override styles specified in the preceding "
"sheets. So you have a \"blank sheet\" here for your own customizations."
msgstr "As a matter of course, the last style sheet to load on every Plone page is ploneCustom.css. You'll see this if you inspect the HTML head tag of your page using Firebug. If you dig further, you'll probably find that this style sheet is completely empty. By the rules of precedence in the CSS Cascade, any styles in this sheet will override styles specified in the preceding sheets. So you have a \"blank sheet\" here for your own customizations."

